TITLE: Creating a ProgramNode Using Helper Function in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of using the programNode helper function to create a new ProgramNode object with specified properties including name, public key, version and empty collections for accounts, instructions, defined types, PDAs, and errors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codama-idl/codama/blob/main/packages/nodes/docs/ProgramNode.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const node = programNode({
    name: 'counter',
    publicKey: '7ovtg4pFqjQdSwFAUCu8gTnh5thZHzAyJFXy3Ssnj3yK',
    version: '1.42.6',
    accounts: [],
    instructions: [],
    definedTypes: [],
    pdas: [],
    errors: [],
});
```

