TITLE: Using parseAccountData Function in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of using the parseAccountData function to identify and deserialize account data from a byte array, showing how to access the parsed data and account node.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codama-idl/codama/blob/main/packages/dynamic-parsers/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const parsedData = parseAccountData(rootNode, bytes);
// ^ ParsedData<AccountNode> | undefined

if (parsedData) {
    const accountNode: AccountNode = getLastNodeFromPath(parsedData.path);
    const decodedData: unknown = parsedData.data;
}
```

