TITLE: Creating an AccountNode with accountNode() Helper Function in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to create a basic AccountNode object using the accountNode() helper function. This creates a 'myCounter' account with authority and value fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codama-idl/codama/blob/main/packages/nodes/docs/AccountNode.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const node = accountNode({
    name: 'myCounter',
    data: structTypeNode([
        structFieldTypeNode({ name: 'authority', type: publicKeyTypeNode() }),
        structFieldTypeNode({ name: 'value', type: numberTypeNode('u64') }),
    ]),
});
```

