TITLE: Setting Instruction Discriminators in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of using setInstructionDiscriminatorsVisitor to add discriminator arguments to specified instructions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codama-idl/codama/blob/main/packages/visitors/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
codama.update(
    setInstructionDiscriminatorsVisitor({
        mint: { name: 'discriminator', type: numberTypeNode('u8'), value: numberValueNode(0) },
        transfer: { name: 'discriminator', type: numberTypeNode('u8'), value: numberValueNode(1) },
        burn: { name: 'discriminator', type: numberTypeNode('u8'), value: numberValueNode(2) },
    }),
);
```

