TITLE: Using Codama Renderers for Multi-Language Code Generation
DESCRIPTION: Example of importing and using different renderers from the @codama/renderers package to generate client code in JavaScript, JavaScript Umi, and Rust. Each renderer is passed a target directory path where the generated code will be placed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codama-idl/codama/blob/main/packages/renderers/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// node ./codama.mjs
import { renderJavaScriptVisitor, renderJavaScriptUmiVisitor, renderRustVisitor } from '@codama/renderers';

codama.accept(renderJavaScriptVisitor('clients/js/src/generated'));
codama.accept(renderJavaScriptUmiVisitor('clients/js-umi/src/generated'));
codama.accept(renderRustVisitor('clients/rust/src/generated'));
