TITLE: Defining a Person Struct with Name and Age in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to create a struct representing a person with a fixed-size UTF-8 string for the name (10 bytes) and an 8-bit unsigned integer for the age. The comment illustrates how the struct is serialized to bytes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codama-idl/codama/blob/main/packages/nodes/docs/typeNodes/StructTypeNode.md#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
structTypeNode([
    structFieldTypeNode({ name: 'name', type: fixedSizeTypeNode(stringTypeNode('utf8'), 10) }),
    structFieldTypeNode({ name: 'age', type: numberTypeNode('u8') }),
]);

// { name: Alice, age: 42 } => 0x416C69636500000000002A
```

